The paper deals with space efficient algorithms for maintaining random samples from large datasets, which is a fundamental problem in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of random bits and weights, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses approximate sampling and lower bounds, which are relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data mining (cs.DM).
